Tel Aviv's Tarbutat café serves as a fragile haven for Israel's progressive camp
subhed: The café, which opened two months after the October 7 attacks, is one of the few places in the country where it is still possible to discuss the reality of the war in Gaza. Conceived as a space shielded from political violence, it has nonetheless become a frequent target of far-right activists.

title: Bedbugs force closure of prestigious Paris cinema
subhed: The Cinémathèque Française, a renowned film archive and cinema, said it would temporarily close its four screening halls for a month from Friday after a series of reported bedbug sightings.

title: Inside the archives of shoemaker Roger Vivier
subhed: This star shoemaker of the 1930s through the 1990s spent his long career experimenting with all kinds of designs. His archives, a testament to his boundless creativity, are now housed in a Parisian hôtel particulier.

title: Gay Talese, the last titan of the American press
subhed: He was a pioneer of New Journalism, a movement that transformed American journalism with a literary writing style. At 93, the author of the landmark 1966 profile 'Frank Sinatra Has a Cold,' finds his daily life increasingly constrained by old age.

title: Israel's D9 bulldozer, a tool of destruction in Gaza
byline: By Liselotte Mas, Elsa Longueville (motion design) and Sinead McCausland
subhed: Imported by the dozens from the United States, Israel has redesigned Caterpillar D9 bulldozers to play a dual strategic and political role: protecting soldiers entering Gaza and leveling the enclave.

title: The difficult conversations between Israeli and Palestinian peace activists
subhed: The anti-occupation NGO Combatants for Peace works to organize joint actions between young people living in the West Bank and in Israel. The group faces the challenge of rebuilding trust between both sides, torn apart by two years of war in Gaza.
